00:27:31,481 --> 00:27:39,422
So let's say the launch date for Ian's Ultimate Indie is on July 1st.

422
00:27:40,444 --> 00:27:42,165
Oh no, we cut off a little bit.

423
00:27:42,165 --> 00:27:42,585
Oh, it's OK.

424
00:27:42,585 --> 00:27:43,586
I can read it to you.

425
00:27:43,586 --> 00:27:44,066
You'll be fine.

426
00:27:44,066 --> 00:27:48,108
This is like a breakdown of what you

427
00:27:48,108 --> 00:27:53,951
need to do in those months before you launch your game.

428
00:27:53,951 --> 00:27:56,593
So this is six months, OK?

429
00:27:56,593 --> 00:28:00,835
And six months sounds like a long time, right?

430
00:28:00,835 --> 00:28:06,718
When you think like, oh, six months is nothing in game dev.

431
00:28:06,718 --> 00:28:09,200
Six months is absolutely nothing.

432
00:28:09,200 --> 00:28:09,500
It's OK.

433
00:28:12,200 --> 00:28:19,447
If you're thinking like, oh I'm going to launch my game in quarter three in 2019.

434
00:28:19,447 --> 00:28:21,769
May-wenty.

435
00:28:21,769 --> 00:28:29,176
You've got three months to get all of this prepared.

436
00:28:29,176 --> 00:28:31,478
And that's quite scary.

437
00:28:32,642 --> 00:28:38,526
In January, you're launching in July, in January you need to have prepared community and social

438
00:28:38,526 --> 00:28:43,649
media, minimal posting, prepare the assets you will need for the launch announcement,

439
00:28:43,649 --> 00:28:45,190
prepare the store page assets.

440
00:28:45,190 --> 00:28:49,573
If you're launching on Steam, you want to make sure that your store page is ready the

441
00:28:49,573 --> 00:28:53,476
minute that you do your launch announcement because you want to get those wish lists because

442
00:28:53,476 --> 00:28:55,297
that's how you get the algorithm to love you.

443
00:28:55,297 --> 00:29:01,041
And you need assets and announcement trailer, okay?

444
00:29:01,041 --> 00:29:02,081
That's month one.

445
00:29:03,135 --> 00:29:08,220
Month two, you need to announce the game, kick off social media, begin funneling people

446
00:29:08,220 --> 00:29:13,025
towards your hood, have the store page go live for wishlisting, release the demo for

447
00:29:13,025 --> 00:29:14,746
press and influencers.

448
00:29:14,746 --> 00:29:21,213
Third month, follow up with those press and influencers, continue developing your community,

449
00:29:21,213 --> 00:29:25,377
pitch new stories, explain why your game is special to people who are interested.

450
00:29:26,122 --> 00:29:31,646
Do a giveaway, give restricted access of the game to your community to get that feedback.

451
00:29:31,646 --> 00:29:34,648
Use your community as beta testers.

452
00:29:34,648 --> 00:29:37,891
Prepare press releases and launch day's announcement.

453
00:29:37,891 --> 00:29:38,931
May.

454
00:29:38,931 --> 00:29:43,035
In May, your game needs to be finished.

455
00:29:43,035 --> 00:29:50,240
So if you are launching in July, your game needs to be finished by the second week of

456
00:29:50,240 --> 00:29:53,463
May in order to give press that six weeks.

457
00:29:54,085 --> 00:29:56,187
of a glorious, glorious...

458
00:29:56,187 --> 00:30:02,350
So you see how quickly that time disappears, right?

459
00:30:02,350 --> 00:30:04,391
Yeah.

460
00:30:04,391 --> 00:30:08,393
So, in May, the first two weeks, you're focusing on finalising the game,

461
00:30:08,393 --> 00:30:11,695
whilst also maintaining community and building up all of that stuff.

462
00:30:11,695 --> 00:30:15,497
Also, and then on the July 1st, sorry, not July 1st,

